  <p class="article-tag" style="margin:0;">NUTRITION</p>
  <h1>High-Protein Diet Plan for Weight Loss: How Much Do You Actually Need?</h1>
  <div class="meta">Last updated: June 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; 9 min read &nbsp;·&nbsp; Reviewed for accuracy</div>

  <p>Protein is the single most important dietary variable for losing fat while keeping muscle. It keeps you fuller for longer, requires more energy to digest than carbs or fat, and provides the amino acids your body needs to maintain lean tissue during a calorie deficit. This guide gives you the exact targets, the best food sources, and a practical meal plan — no supplements required.</p>

  <div class="toc">
    <div class="toc-title">📋 In This Article</div>
    <ol>
      <li><a href="#why-protein">Why Protein Matters More During Weight Loss</a></li>
      <li><a href="#how-much">How Much Protein Do You Actually Need?</a></li>
